## 10. Closeout criteria

1. 4 fixtures × 10,000 grid pts × 2 formats × 4 degrees worth of measurements emitted (or comparable, with some combinations N/A).
2. All 5 predictions audited.
3. Failure modes named.
4. Verdict: theorem extension (strict P_S1 holds) / theorem sharp (transition exists) / theorem partial.
5. If theorem extends: strengthened theorem statement formalized for closeout.
6. If theorem sharp: transition location characterized.
7. Reproducibility: byte-stable artifact.
8. Phase next follow-ups.

## 11. Out of scope

- Subnormal / overflow extremes (proviso of theorem; we sample only x_term in [1e-3, 1−1e-3]).
- Non-binary float formats (decimal, posit).
- FMA-based variants of the multiplication chain.
- Algebraic-tree variations (right-to-left vs left-to-right).
- Generalization beyond `R^n + (x_term − 1)` structure.

